Continental, Draxlmaier May Invest 169 Million Euros in Romania

-- B y   I r i n a   S a v u
-- 
2011-09-23T13:10:09Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-23/continental-draxlmaier-may-invest-169-million-euros-in-romania.html
German car-parts makers  Continental
AG (CON)  and Draxlmaier AG may invest as much as 169 million euros
($228 million) in  Romania  through 2013, the Balkan country’s
economy ministry said after meetings with the two companies.  Continental,  Europe ’s second-biggest car-parts maker, will
invest 15.7 million euros to expand Contitech Fluid Automotive
Romania’s plant and 71 million euros in 2012 and 2013 to expand
its unit in the western Romanian city of Timisoara, the ministry
said in an e-mailed statement today. It will also invest about
35 million euros in a unit in the central town of Sibiu and 20
million euros in a fuel-pump plant in the central town of
Brasov.  Romania’s Economy Minister Ion Ariton also met with
Draxlmaier’s management who are considering investing 26.8
million euros in a unit in the eastern European country,
according to the statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Irina Savu in Bucharest at 
